# Food Website Project

## Project Overview
This project is a responsive food website built using HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap. It features a visually appealing layout with various sections that highlight the menu, services, and unique selling points of the food business. The design includes a banner, navigation bar, and different sections showcasing menu items and service features.

## Features
- **Responsive Design:** The website is fully responsive and adjusts seamlessly across different devices and screen sizes.
- **Navigation Bar:** Includes links to different sections like "Why Choose Us?", "Explore Menu", "Delivery & Payment", and "Follow Us".
- **Banner Section:** A visually captivating banner with a call-to-action for viewing the menu and placing orders.
- **Why Choose Us Section:** Highlights the unique selling points of the food service with descriptive cards.
- **Explore Menu Section:** Showcases various menu items with images and descriptions.
- **Custom Buttons and Styling:** Custom-styled buttons and links to enhance user interaction.

## Technologies Used
- **HTML5:** For structuring the webpage.
- **CSS3:** For styling and layout.
- **Bootstrap 5.3:** For responsive design and pre-built components.
- **Google Fonts:** For the "Roboto" font used across the website.
- **Freepik Images:** For high-quality images used in the banner and menu sections.

## Installation
1. Clone the repository:
    ```bash
    git clone <repository-url>
    ```
2. Navigate to the project directory:
    ```bash
    cd food-website
    ```
3. Open the `index.html` file in your web browser to view the website.

## Usage
- Navigate through the website using the navigation bar.
- Explore the banner section for a quick introduction and call-to-action buttons.
- Check out the "Why Choose Us" section to understand the unique services offered.
- Browse through the "Explore Menu" section to view various food items with images and descriptions.

## Customization
- To customize the website, you can edit the `index.html` file for content changes.
- Modify the `style` tag or external CSS files for styling adjustments.
- Update image URLs or replace them with your own images.

